CAPE TOWN - More than 500 people who lost their homes and their belongings in a fire in Valhalla Park outside Cape TownÂ spent the night in a community hall in the area. It is believed the fire broke out after a cooking stove fell over in one of the homes on Boxing Day morning. The fire destroyed around 150 structures. WATCH: Bleak Christmas on cards for homeless Durban shack-dwellers No fatalities or injuries were reported. The City of Cape Town said it is currently clearing the site to prepare for rebuilding. It will also provide building material to the victims to rebuild their destroyed homes. eNCA